    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>ONLINE AUCTION MERGER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>QXL PLC, Britain's biggest online auctioneer, agrees to buy Ricardo.de AG, German rival, for $1 billion in stock, premium of 27 percent; combination will be known as QXLricardo PLC and will have 1.3 million members (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Under challenge from eBay Inc. in Europe's Internet auction business, Britain's biggest online auctioneer QXL P.L.C. agreed to buy Ricardo.de A.G., a German rival, for $1 billion in stock, a premium of 27 percent. The London-based combination will be known as QXLricardo P.L.C. and will have 1.3 million members. EBay already sells more goods in Europe than the British and German companies combined.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
